        -:   21:// Computes a power field on the entire mesh from given values at the prescribed indices.
        -:   22:// If no constraints are given the lowest-eigenvalue (of smoothness energy) field will be returned.
        -:   23:// Input:
        -:   24://  tb: underlying tangent bundle.
        -:   25://  constFaces: the faces on which the polyvector is prescribed. If a face is repeated and the alignment is hard then all but the first vector in the face will be ignored.
        -:   26://  constVectors: #F by 3 in representative form of the N-RoSy's on the tangent spaces.
        -:   27://  alignWeights: #constFaces x 1 soft weights for alignment (negative values = fixed faces).
        -:   28://  N: The degree of the field.
        -:   29:// Output:
        -:   30://  powerField: a cartesian power-field object.
